extractCountsLine

Gets the number of atoms and bonds from the fourth line of the MOL string.

extractAtoms

private void extractAtoms()
Interprets the "atom block" of the Mol String. Each line should contain data for one atom. Extracts an Atom object from each line of the Mol String and adds each atom to the atom list.

extractBonds

private void extractBonds()
Interprets the "bond block" of the Mol String. Each line should contain data for one bond. Extracts a Bond object from each line of the Mol String and adds each bond to the bond list.

extractProperties

private void extractProperties()
Interprets the PROPERTY block of the Mol String. Each line contains data on one property which contains information for 1 to 8 items (atoms or bonds). End of property block is marked by "M END"

extractPropertyLine

private boolean extractPropertyLine(String line)
Extracts property data from the line. If it is an END line, simply return true indicating END was found. If a regular property, extract data from the line and apply it to the data structure.

Parameters:
line - a property line from the MOL string (CHG, LNE, CLA, CLB, END, etc.)
Returns:
true if property is END

extractPropertyTag

private String extractPropertyTag(String line)
Validate the beginning of a property line and gets the three-character property tag. Beginning of line should be "M ppp" where ppp is the property tag.

Parameters:
line - a property line from the MOL string
Returns:
the three-character tag if found, or empty string if tag not found.

molChargeCodeToCharge

private int molChargeCodeToCharge(int molCode)
Gets a charge value for the atom block. These codes are placed on an Atom Line in the Atom Block. The documentation says these are deprecated and ignored, but are included for backward compatibility with "old" mol file interpreters. Officially, if any M__CHG line occurs in the property block, this value is ignored.

Parameters:
molCode - the charge code
Returns:
the actual charge
